</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[167,776,1762,1989]" pageId="17" pageNumber="644">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,330,1762,1786]" pageId="17" pageNumber="644">Identification.</emphasis>
This species can be identified by a small depressed pileus with greyish tones, whitish lamellae, a dark stipe, and ellipsoid spores of 6–9 × 3–5 µm. Our material agrees with the description provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pegler DN" pageId="17" pageNumber="644" refId="ref17566" refString="Pegler DN (1983) Agaric flora of the Lesser Antilles. Marston Book Services, London, 721 pp." type="book" year="1983">Pegler (1983)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Berk. &amp; M. A. Curtis)" baseAuthorityName="Berk. &amp; M. A. Curtis" box="[246,751,1897,1922]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Gerronema" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="17" pageNumber="644" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="cyathiforme">
<emphasis box="[246,506,1897,1921]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="644">Gerronema cyathiforme</emphasis>
(Berk. &amp; M.A. Curtis)
</taxonomicName>
is a similar species but differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[523,664,1931,1955]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Gerronema" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="17" pageNumber="644" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="bryogeton">
<emphasis box="[523,664,1931,1955]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="644">G. bryogeton</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a reddish to olivaceous brown stipe (
<bibRefCitation author="Pegler DN" box="[561,692,1965,1989]" pageId="17" pageNumber="644" refId="ref17566" refString="Pegler DN (1983) Agaric flora of the Lesser Antilles. Marston Book Services, London, 721 pp." type="book" year="1983">Pegler 1983</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
